cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses a solution for self-interference cancellation in in-band full duplex wireless communication, which involves signal processing, wireless networking, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data communication and signal processing. The paper also involves wireless networking, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed solution is based on deep learning, which suggests the involvement of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the solution is implemented on a testbed, which involves system-level considerations and falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
